WEBVTT

00:01.433 --> 00:02.766
♪ ♪

00:02.766 --> 00:04.066
CLARA:
Laudanum!

00:04.066 --> 00:06.166
I didn't agree to poison her!

00:06.166 --> 00:07.266
♪ ♪

00:07.266 --> 00:09.666
CHARLES:
I'm not doing this for money,

00:09.666 --> 00:11.966
but for love.

00:11.966 --> 00:14.033
FRASER:
I say to you now
in all sincerity,

00:14.033 --> 00:16.066
you have never
looked lovelier.

00:16.066 --> 00:17.866
COLBOURNE:
Lucy and I married young.

00:17.866 --> 00:19.333
She wanted to stay in London.

00:19.333 --> 00:20.500
CHARLOTTE:
That's where she met
Colonel Lennox.

00:20.500 --> 00:22.400
COLBOURNE:
I went to London,

00:22.400 --> 00:24.133
only to find
she was with child.

00:24.133 --> 00:25.366
His child?

00:25.366 --> 00:29.633
♪ ♪

00:30.933 --> 00:35.500
♪ ♪

00:41.166 --> 00:45.466
♪ ♪

00:51.266 --> 00:54.833
♪ ♪

00:56.200 --> 01:01.400
♪ ♪

01:11.266 --> 01:16.400
♪ ♪

01:26.033 --> 01:27.733
(seagulls squawking)

01:27.733 --> 01:31.733
(people talking in background)

01:31.733 --> 01:36.900
♪ ♪

01:45.800 --> 01:48.133
(hoofbeats resume)

01:48.133 --> 01:51.433
So it was the colonel that stole
Mr. Colbourne's wife?

01:51.433 --> 01:53.600
He's the villain of the story,
not the victim?

01:53.600 --> 01:56.933
Mr. Colbourne is not at all the
man I had been led to believe.

01:56.933 --> 01:59.133
ALISON:
I cannot believe
how the colonel treated you.

01:59.133 --> 02:01.300
I shall never forgive myself.

02:01.300 --> 02:03.100
All these weeks, we've been
urging you to consider him.

02:03.100 --> 02:04.133
Last night,

02:04.133 --> 02:05.933
we insisted you dance with him.

02:05.933 --> 02:07.300
We were all deceived.

02:07.300 --> 02:08.766
ALISON:
It seems I'm a woeful
judge of character,

02:08.766 --> 02:11.466
at least where gentlemen
are concerned.

02:11.466 --> 02:13.733
Perhaps there's a lesson
to be drawn.

02:13.733 --> 02:15.566
Soldiers are not to be trusted.

02:15.566 --> 02:16.600
Better stick to...

02:16.600 --> 02:18.766
Artists?

02:18.766 --> 02:21.133
For example.
(chuckles)

02:21.133 --> 02:23.100
ALISON:
Not all soldiers
are untrustworthy.

02:23.100 --> 02:26.200
I know one who is in every way
admirable.

02:26.200 --> 02:28.366
I cannot think who you mean.

02:28.366 --> 02:30.300
ALISON:
I think I shall miss him
more than anyone else

02:30.300 --> 02:34.700
I have met here.

02:34.700 --> 02:37.200
Is it not peculiar?

02:37.200 --> 02:39.600
How we can be strangers
to our own affections?

02:39.600 --> 02:41.433
♪ ♪

02:41.433 --> 02:43.466
It isn't peculiar at all.

02:43.466 --> 02:46.933
♪ ♪

02:46.933 --> 02:48.300
(birds squawking)

02:48.300 --> 02:49.733
FUCHS:
I was witness

02:49.733 --> 02:54.633
to your behavior at the ball
last night, meine Dame.

02:54.633 --> 02:57.033
We were all greatly concerned.

02:58.266 --> 03:00.033
Und when you returned,

03:00.033 --> 03:03.033
I am told you tried
to take the baby.

03:03.033 --> 03:05.500
(weakly):
No.

03:05.500 --> 03:07.600
I would never hurt my child.

03:07.600 --> 03:09.766
FUCHS:
Your child?

03:13.700 --> 03:16.533
I did not mean...

03:16.533 --> 03:18.566
My dear Lady Babington.

03:18.566 --> 03:21.200
You have to help me, Doctor.

03:21.200 --> 03:25.233
I cannot tell
what is real

03:25.233 --> 03:30.166
and what is the work
of my imagination.

03:30.166 --> 03:33.600
Sometimes I want to
dash my head against the wall

03:33.600 --> 03:36.433
to rid myself
of these thoughts.

03:36.433 --> 03:40.466
(crying)

03:40.466 --> 03:43.833
(groans)

03:43.833 --> 03:49.100
♪ ♪

03:49.100 --> 03:50.433
(Fuchs sighs)

03:54.366 --> 03:58.166
(horse whinnying outside)

03:58.166 --> 04:03.033
♪ ♪

04:03.033 --> 04:06.200
(doorbell ringing)

04:11.200 --> 04:12.433
Miss Heywood.

04:12.433 --> 04:13.533
I thought I might have
missed you.

04:13.533 --> 04:15.800
Will you come in?

04:15.800 --> 04:17.966
Thank you.

04:17.966 --> 04:21.266
(door closes)
What I have to say will
only take a moment.

04:23.866 --> 04:25.166
(exhales):
I'm not a man

04:25.166 --> 04:28.466
adept at expressing
his feelings, Miss Heywood.

04:28.466 --> 04:31.066
Honesty has an eloquence
of its own,

04:31.066 --> 04:33.533
don't you think?

04:33.533 --> 04:37.000
Then let me just say that

04:37.000 --> 04:38.200
these past few weeks,

04:38.200 --> 04:40.466
I have grown to...

04:45.766 --> 04:47.400
...to consider you a friend.

04:47.400 --> 04:53.933
And so, I came to
offer you this token,

04:53.933 --> 04:55.800
something to
remember me by.

04:57.900 --> 05:00.000
♪ ♪

05:00.000 --> 05:01.333
Only...

05:01.333 --> 05:03.866
Do not open it until you are
returned to Willingden.

05:03.866 --> 05:05.966
Will you promise?

05:05.966 --> 05:09.166
I promise.

05:09.166 --> 05:10.400
Well.

05:10.400 --> 05:13.700
Goodbye, then.

05:15.400 --> 05:21.166
♪ ♪

05:22.100 --> 05:23.066
Goodbye.

05:23.066 --> 05:27.900
♪ ♪

05:31.533 --> 05:32.933
Damn!

05:32.933 --> 05:37.000
(seagulls squawking)

05:37.000 --> 05:39.266
I fear she's become a danger
not only to herself,

05:39.266 --> 05:40.933
but to those
around her.

05:40.933 --> 05:43.300
FUCHS:
That you have asked me here

05:43.300 --> 05:44.666
the morning of your wedding,

05:44.666 --> 05:47.633
Kapitän Denham, speaks of
the depths of your concern.

05:47.633 --> 05:50.333
And you are right
to be alarmed.

05:50.333 --> 05:54.433
I believe her hysteria
has advanced beyond

05:54.433 --> 05:56.033
the point of no return.

05:56.033 --> 05:57.333
LADY DENHAM:
Oh, nonsense!

05:57.333 --> 06:00.800
There must be some treatment
we can find to shock her

06:00.800 --> 06:01.966
out of this malaise.

06:01.966 --> 06:05.933
This is no malaise, milady!

06:05.933 --> 06:11.433
Alas, I fear the time has come
for drastic action!

06:11.433 --> 06:13.300
You don't mean...

06:14.500 --> 06:15.566
Not an institution.

06:15.566 --> 06:21.933
♪ ♪

06:21.933 --> 06:23.833
BEATRICE:
I see you have been packing up

06:23.833 --> 06:25.466
your materials,
Mr. Lockhart.

06:25.466 --> 06:27.900
You are not leaving us?

06:27.900 --> 06:30.233
Alas, yes, Miss Hankins.

06:30.233 --> 06:31.800
This very day.

06:31.800 --> 06:33.166
What a great shame!

06:33.166 --> 06:35.000
I've a restless soul.

06:35.000 --> 06:39.400
And where will that restless
soul be taking you next?

06:39.400 --> 06:41.266
I shall be touring
the continent.

06:41.266 --> 06:43.000
With a dear companion.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
A friend?

06:45.000 --> 06:48.100
Rather more than a friend.

06:48.100 --> 06:49.333
BEATRICE:
Congratulations,

06:49.333 --> 06:50.800
Mr. Lockhart!

06:50.800 --> 06:53.166
And who is the
fortunate young lady?

06:53.166 --> 06:54.600
Suffice it to say,

06:54.600 --> 06:59.200
she is the most inspiring muse
an artist could wish for.

07:01.833 --> 07:06.333
♪ ♪

07:06.333 --> 07:07.300
It is done.

07:07.300 --> 07:11.333
♪ ♪

07:18.133 --> 07:19.166
Well, Miss Lambe?

07:19.166 --> 07:22.766
Have I captured you?

07:22.766 --> 07:25.300
Utterly.

07:25.300 --> 07:28.433
♪ ♪

07:28.433 --> 07:30.400
I've been doing
some calculations.

07:30.400 --> 07:32.233
Here's the total owed
to our shopkeepers

07:32.233 --> 07:34.200
and hostelries
by the colonel and his men.

07:34.200 --> 07:36.433
And this is your debt
to the colonel.

07:36.433 --> 07:37.466
Mary...

07:37.466 --> 07:39.333
Apologies serve little purpose,
Tom.

07:39.333 --> 07:41.166
Right now, we need to decide
what is to be done.

07:41.166 --> 07:42.233
We must simply borrow

07:42.233 --> 07:44.333
from the children's savings.
FOOTMAN:
Sir.

07:45.433 --> 07:49.766
♪ ♪

07:49.766 --> 07:53.366
Oh, Sidney's
possessions.

07:53.366 --> 07:55.500
At last.

07:57.033 --> 07:58.900
(stammers):
Have it set down
in the study.

07:58.900 --> 08:01.000
Certainly, sir.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.100
♪ ♪

08:03.100 --> 08:08.266
(birds twittering)

08:11.433 --> 08:13.500
(sighs)

08:13.500 --> 08:20.733
♪ ♪

08:30.466 --> 08:35.933
♪ ♪

08:37.500 --> 08:38.833
Miss Heywood.

08:40.066 --> 08:42.833
I wondered if we might take
a turn about the grounds.

08:47.933 --> 08:49.333
EDWARD:
Our work is all but done.

08:49.333 --> 08:52.533
Babington will return to find
his wife half-mad in the asylum.

08:52.533 --> 08:53.766
The asylum?!

08:54.766 --> 08:57.000
We must be sure
we're rid of her for good.

08:57.000 --> 08:58.466
We cannot let her
take our money.

08:58.466 --> 09:00.433
George's money.

09:03.133 --> 09:04.366
Of course.

09:04.366 --> 09:08.700
Keep her glass full
at our wedding breakfast.

09:08.700 --> 09:11.533
She will want to toast
our happiness.

09:11.533 --> 09:12.533
(softly):
Yes, she will.

09:12.533 --> 09:16.666
♪ ♪

09:18.833 --> 09:20.966
(door opens)

09:23.400 --> 09:24.666
(door closes)

09:31.633 --> 09:36.566
♪ ♪

09:41.333 --> 09:43.500
He'd want you to have it.

09:52.533 --> 09:58.100
♪ ♪

09:58.100 --> 10:00.500
His playing cards.

10:00.500 --> 10:02.466
I always hoped that I might
one day beat him

10:02.466 --> 10:03.866
at vingt-et-un.

10:06.666 --> 10:08.100
Brother.

10:08.100 --> 10:12.033
It's Sidney's handwriting.

10:12.033 --> 10:17.233
♪ ♪

10:17.233 --> 10:20.266
(birds twittering)

10:20.266 --> 10:22.466
(Luna barking)

10:24.666 --> 10:28.833
I have been thinking on
our conversation last night.

10:28.833 --> 10:30.700
I must apologize.

10:30.700 --> 10:31.966
I said too much.

10:31.966 --> 10:32.966
I beg you never speak of it.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.133
I won't breathe a word.

10:37.233 --> 10:41.466
I too have known heartache
and betrayal.

10:44.000 --> 10:45.666
I had sworn off
love and marriage.

10:45.666 --> 10:49.866
And yet I have come to realize

10:49.866 --> 10:52.366
I cannot hide myself away.

10:54.266 --> 10:58.266
I must live my life.

10:58.266 --> 11:00.000
Is it not time
you did the same?

11:00.000 --> 11:03.500
♪ ♪

11:08.800 --> 11:10.233
MRS. WHEATLEY:
Mr. Colbourne!

11:10.233 --> 11:12.000
Mr. Colbourne!

11:14.100 --> 11:16.333
It is Miss Leonora, sir.

11:16.333 --> 11:18.366
She is nowhere
to be found.

11:20.633 --> 11:23.566
TOM (voiceover):
"I fear I am gravely ill
and lack the strength to write

11:23.566 --> 11:25.000
"all that I wish to,

11:25.000 --> 11:27.833
"but suffice to say that
you must bear no guilt

11:27.833 --> 11:30.800
"for my part in saving you
from ruin.

11:32.466 --> 11:34.233
"If you wish to honor my memory,

11:34.233 --> 11:38.366
"you must hold fast
to your vision.

11:38.366 --> 11:41.466
"Don't be afraid
to keep on taking risks...

11:44.466 --> 11:47.466
(voice breaking):
...or what is life for?"

11:47.466 --> 11:50.600
I left my purse behind.
Mm.

11:50.600 --> 11:51.600
I'll only be a moment.

11:51.600 --> 11:53.700
Mm.

11:53.700 --> 11:55.266
TOM (voiceover):
"But the most urgent matter

11:55.266 --> 11:57.066
"I must impress upon you

11:57.066 --> 12:00.900
"is the need to protect
Georgiana

12:00.900 --> 12:03.433
"from the man who has been
seeking to claim her fortune.

12:03.433 --> 12:06.666
"He is a man quite
without scruple.

12:06.666 --> 12:09.300
"His name...

12:09.300 --> 12:10.833
...is Charles Lockhart."

12:10.833 --> 12:12.500
(both gasp)

12:12.500 --> 12:18.566
♪ ♪

12:18.566 --> 12:21.033
We have every last member
of staff combing the estate.

12:21.033 --> 12:23.133
We've already searched
every inch of the house.

12:23.133 --> 12:25.500
She can't have disappeared
into thin air!

12:25.500 --> 12:27.666
Leo!

12:30.666 --> 12:32.866
Augusta.

12:33.966 --> 12:35.733
(keys jangling)

12:35.733 --> 12:37.900
I gave her my word.

12:37.900 --> 12:39.433
Augusta,
for God's sake...

12:39.433 --> 12:41.000
It's all right.

12:43.666 --> 12:45.666
She woke me up late last night.

12:45.666 --> 12:46.866
She, she was crying.

12:48.166 --> 12:49.733
She said she overheard
you talking.

12:49.733 --> 12:51.633
Something about Colonel Lennox.

12:51.633 --> 12:54.800
She's gone to
speak with him.

12:56.533 --> 13:01.966
♪ ♪

13:06.500 --> 13:11.233
♪ ♪

13:17.966 --> 13:21.600
Are you here to enlist?

13:24.100 --> 13:28.200
I wish to speak with
Colonel Lennox.

13:32.166 --> 13:33.266
Hm.

13:33.266 --> 13:38.433
♪ ♪

13:40.633 --> 13:43.266
(wings fluttering above)

13:43.266 --> 13:45.366
HANKINS:
Are we expecting more guests

13:45.366 --> 13:46.933
to join us at the church?

13:46.933 --> 13:48.300
Oh, certainly not.

13:48.300 --> 13:52.266
We want this ceremony to be as
swift and discreet as possible.

13:52.266 --> 13:54.566
Ah, well, to your first point,
milady,

13:54.566 --> 13:57.666
I have chosen hymns of no more
than five or six verses

13:57.666 --> 14:01.666
which I shall instruct
my sister to play allegro.

14:01.666 --> 14:03.366
And I shall limit my sermon

14:03.366 --> 14:04.766
to just half an hour.

14:04.766 --> 14:06.033
Hymns are not required.

14:06.033 --> 14:09.100
And we can certainly
live without the sermon.

14:09.100 --> 14:12.600
A funeral liturgy might be
more apt.

14:14.933 --> 14:17.000
Forgive Lady Babington,
Mr. Hankins.

14:17.000 --> 14:19.300
She's not entirely herself.

14:22.200 --> 14:24.233
We must drink a toast.

14:24.233 --> 14:26.200
LADY DENHAM:
What shall we drink to?

14:26.200 --> 14:28.533
May your union be blessed

14:28.533 --> 14:30.600
with children.
(Lady Denham chuckles)

14:30.600 --> 14:33.666
A little late after the fact,
I'm afraid.

14:35.166 --> 14:36.833
To my beautiful wife, Clara.

14:36.833 --> 14:39.433
Thank you for making
an honest man of me.

14:39.433 --> 14:40.833
CLARA:
No, Esther.

14:41.933 --> 14:43.266
LADY DENHAM:
Oh, Clara's right.

14:43.266 --> 14:44.600
After last night's debacle,

14:44.600 --> 14:46.633
perhaps you'd better abstain,
Esther.

14:46.633 --> 14:48.200
Oh, one drink won't harm.

14:50.333 --> 14:52.000
(smashes loudly,
Lady Denham cries out)

14:52.000 --> 14:55.333
♪ ♪

14:55.333 --> 14:57.733
Will you admit the truth,
Edward?

14:57.733 --> 15:00.000
Or shall I?

15:00.000 --> 15:03.233
♪ ♪

15:05.433 --> 15:09.300
♪ ♪

15:13.033 --> 15:14.133
BEATRICE:
Miss Lambe?

15:14.133 --> 15:17.266
You have visitors.

15:21.766 --> 15:23.166
What is it?

15:29.133 --> 15:32.400
He set out to convince you
you were insane.

15:33.733 --> 15:35.166
He took your
deepest vulnerabilities

15:35.166 --> 15:38.100
and he exploited them.

15:39.533 --> 15:41.833
To my eternal shame,

15:41.833 --> 15:45.000
I have not only
remained silent,

15:45.000 --> 15:47.866
but I have aided him
in his cruelty.

15:47.866 --> 15:49.400
(pounds):
This is preposterous!

15:49.400 --> 15:51.300
You cannot believe her.

15:54.966 --> 15:59.900
I told myself it was
for the sake of our son.

15:59.900 --> 16:03.566
That you stood in the way
of his inheritance.

16:04.766 --> 16:08.866
We have stolen every letter
that Babington has sent you.

16:08.866 --> 16:10.733
(exhales)

16:10.733 --> 16:11.866
We have led you

16:11.866 --> 16:17.033
to doubt the evidence
of your own eyes.

16:17.033 --> 16:21.666
And Dr. Fuchs's tincture...

16:24.533 --> 16:27.933
...the tincture you placed
your hope in,

16:27.933 --> 16:30.900
we replaced with this--

16:30.900 --> 16:33.133
laudanum.

16:33.133 --> 16:34.566
EDWARD:
Can't you see what
she's doing with these lies?

16:34.566 --> 16:36.866
She's trying to turn us
against each other!

16:36.866 --> 16:40.400
You asked for forgiveness
and I gave it!

16:40.400 --> 16:42.600
You asked for shelter

16:42.600 --> 16:45.000
and I gave it!

16:45.000 --> 16:48.400
I chose to believe
your remorse was genuine!

16:48.400 --> 16:50.866
More fool me!

16:50.866 --> 16:52.333
You're despicable,

16:52.333 --> 16:53.600
the pair of you.

16:53.600 --> 16:57.033
I can think of no punishment
severe enough!

16:57.033 --> 16:58.566
No, Aunt.

17:00.266 --> 17:04.966
Clara deserves
no punishment.

17:04.966 --> 17:08.833
She is as much
his victim as I am.

17:11.233 --> 17:13.366
We cannot cast her out.

17:16.666 --> 17:20.666
For George's sake,
as much as hers.

17:20.666 --> 17:24.500
(inhales, groans softly)

17:24.500 --> 17:29.733
♪ ♪

17:34.300 --> 17:37.166
LEONORA:
This one is a colonel,
like you.

17:37.166 --> 17:40.366
He commands a battalion
of a thousand men.

17:40.366 --> 17:43.666
If I were a boy,
I would be a colonel, too.

17:43.666 --> 17:46.366
Or maybe a duke.

17:46.366 --> 17:48.600
Do your parents know
you're here?

17:48.600 --> 17:52.266
I do not have "parents."

17:52.266 --> 17:53.266
My mother is dead.

17:53.266 --> 17:55.433
I'm sorry to hear that.

17:55.433 --> 17:57.700
It was not long after
I was born.

17:57.700 --> 17:58.833
I never knew her.

18:00.266 --> 18:01.633
But you did.

18:01.633 --> 18:03.433
(scoffs)

18:03.433 --> 18:06.000
Her name was
Lucy Colbourne.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.433
♪ ♪

18:08.433 --> 18:09.666
I wanted to meet you

18:09.666 --> 18:14.166
to see if it's true
that you are my real father.

18:17.166 --> 18:18.566
How, how old are you?

18:18.566 --> 18:20.300
I shall be nine
in October.

18:20.300 --> 18:21.966
(footsteps approaching)

18:21.966 --> 18:23.833
I beg your pardon,
Colonel.
Leo!

18:25.466 --> 18:26.566
LEONORA:
Well, sir?

18:26.566 --> 18:27.766
Are you?

18:27.766 --> 18:34.733
♪ ♪

18:39.133 --> 18:41.266
No.

18:42.266 --> 18:43.766
No, I'm not.

18:43.766 --> 18:44.733
That man is your father.

18:44.733 --> 18:49.766
♪ ♪

18:58.166 --> 19:02.433
♪ ♪

19:04.233 --> 19:05.333
COLBOURNE (voiceover):
Why did you not

19:05.333 --> 19:06.266
come and talk to me?

19:06.266 --> 19:09.033
I thought
you'd be angry.

19:09.033 --> 19:11.400
No, no,
I'm not angry.

19:11.400 --> 19:12.933
But whatever you thought
you heard,

19:12.933 --> 19:14.566
I am your father,

19:14.566 --> 19:15.800
and I always will be.

19:15.800 --> 19:17.500
But last night...

19:17.500 --> 19:19.566
All I meant was that
I have not been the father

19:19.566 --> 19:20.566
that you deserve.

19:20.566 --> 19:22.266
But I will endeavor
to be better,

19:22.266 --> 19:23.933
I give you my word.

19:23.933 --> 19:26.800
LEONORA:
I'm glad it's you.

19:26.800 --> 19:29.166
Even though you're not
a colonel, I was sad to think

19:29.166 --> 19:32.166
I might not be your daughter.

19:33.466 --> 19:35.766
♪ ♪

19:35.766 --> 19:37.766
(breath trembles)

19:37.766 --> 19:41.466
♪ ♪

19:41.466 --> 19:43.533
COLBOURNE:
Will you take her home?

19:43.533 --> 19:45.300
I need a last word
with the colonel.

19:48.266 --> 19:50.000
Of course.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.233
Thank you.

19:52.233 --> 19:58.033
♪ ♪

20:05.633 --> 20:08.633
Shall we ask if her sister
has left yet?

20:08.633 --> 20:10.333
I have said my farewell.

20:10.333 --> 20:11.500
I've always
looked up to you, Fraser.

20:11.500 --> 20:13.433
For the first time
in your life,

20:13.433 --> 20:15.666
you are acting
like a coward.

20:15.666 --> 20:20.433
♪ ♪

20:30.333 --> 20:32.500
(birds twittering)

20:38.300 --> 20:40.866
I came to thank you.

20:40.866 --> 20:42.766
For sparing Leonora the truth.

20:42.766 --> 20:45.566
What good would have come of it?
(exhales)

20:45.566 --> 20:47.900
I only hope you take
better care of her

20:47.900 --> 20:49.733
than you did of her mother.

20:52.600 --> 20:54.133
Whatever you told Miss
Heywood...

20:54.133 --> 20:56.433
I remember the state
Lucy was in

20:56.433 --> 20:58.666
when I first met her.

20:58.666 --> 21:01.033
Lost.

21:01.033 --> 21:02.200
Abandoned.

21:04.100 --> 21:06.000
I know I could have been
a better husband.

21:06.000 --> 21:09.000
But I never abandoned her.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.633
It was you who preyed upon
her vulnerabilities.

21:11.633 --> 21:12.666
It was you

21:12.666 --> 21:13.700
who made a victim
of her.

21:13.700 --> 21:15.166
All I did was offer her

21:15.166 --> 21:18.266
the comfort her husband
couldn't.

21:18.266 --> 21:22.900
♪ ♪

21:22.900 --> 21:26.466
You know
I speak the truth.

21:26.466 --> 21:28.900
Miss Heywood's plainly
in love with you.

21:28.900 --> 21:31.233
Can you trust yourself not to
fail her as you failed Lucy?

21:31.233 --> 21:38.000
♪ ♪

21:41.800 --> 21:44.900
You are not fit
to speak their names.

21:47.033 --> 21:52.733
(horses trotting,
people talking in background)

21:55.933 --> 21:57.466
(laughs)

21:57.466 --> 21:59.133
I was beginning to fear

21:59.133 --> 22:01.733
you would not come.

22:01.733 --> 22:03.900
Are you sure
you still wish to marry me?

22:03.900 --> 22:07.033
Given that I am

22:07.033 --> 22:09.266
the mulatto daughter
of a slave

22:09.266 --> 22:12.300
who conspired to claim
the fortune

22:12.300 --> 22:14.966
of a white man
who is not even my father.

22:14.966 --> 22:18.733
That was your argument,
was it not?

22:18.733 --> 22:19.700
Georgiana...

22:19.700 --> 22:21.600
That because you
are his nephew,

22:21.600 --> 22:24.000
you have a greater claim
to my fortune than I.

22:24.000 --> 22:29.366
♪ ♪

22:29.366 --> 22:30.666
(softly):
May we talk apart...

22:30.666 --> 22:32.266
This was always your plan.

22:32.266 --> 22:33.833
Your suit had failed,

22:33.833 --> 22:36.766
so you thought to gain
my money by marrying me.

22:38.466 --> 22:39.933
Was any of it real?

22:39.933 --> 22:41.066
Yes!

22:43.300 --> 22:44.633
The more I have grown
to know you,

22:44.633 --> 22:47.500
the more I have come
to ardently admire you.

22:48.866 --> 22:49.866
Things needn't change.

22:49.866 --> 22:51.266
We can still marry,

22:51.266 --> 22:53.300
still travel the world.

22:53.300 --> 22:56.100
Can you honestly say that
you would rather remain here

22:56.100 --> 22:58.966
in this stifling place,
with these preposterous people?

22:58.966 --> 23:01.000
We may be preposterous,

23:01.000 --> 23:02.900
Mr. Lockhart,

23:02.900 --> 23:07.966
but we are honest
and sincere.

23:09.100 --> 23:11.933
These people have shown me
a kindness a man like you

23:11.933 --> 23:13.166
could never understand.

23:13.166 --> 23:15.366
TOM:
Leave, Mr. Lockhart.

23:15.366 --> 23:17.500
Now.

23:18.366 --> 23:23.533
♪ ♪

23:26.933 --> 23:28.766
I've been considering

23:28.766 --> 23:32.466
which punishment
best fits your crime.

23:32.466 --> 23:34.600
I will spare you
the trouble.

23:34.600 --> 23:36.800
I assume I'm banished forever.

23:37.700 --> 23:38.800
What is the point

23:38.800 --> 23:41.100
in throwing you out

23:41.100 --> 23:44.800
when you will only return
like the bad penny you are?

23:45.866 --> 23:48.133
So, instead, I propose

23:48.133 --> 23:50.566
a vigorous program of reform.

23:50.566 --> 23:55.400
You will submit to hard labor,
religious instruction,

23:55.400 --> 23:58.366
and whatever daily humiliations

23:58.366 --> 24:00.400
I can devise.

24:00.400 --> 24:02.066
And in return,

24:02.066 --> 24:06.133
once I am satisfied that you are
genuinely repentant,

24:06.133 --> 24:07.933
I will consider

24:07.933 --> 24:11.433
a small monthly allowance.

24:18.633 --> 24:21.800
I would sooner die in battle.

24:24.233 --> 24:27.166
(chuckling)

24:27.166 --> 24:29.900
(people talking in background,
seagulls squawking)

24:29.900 --> 24:32.033
(horse nickers)

24:37.433 --> 24:39.133
Now that we have dealt
with one

24:39.133 --> 24:42.100
treacherous interloper,
we must deal with the other.

24:42.100 --> 24:44.000
But how?

24:44.000 --> 24:46.200
What would Sidney say,

24:46.200 --> 24:50.000
were he standing here
instead of me?

24:51.533 --> 24:53.033
He would tell me
the only way to conquer

24:53.033 --> 24:56.300
a man like the colonel

24:56.300 --> 24:58.000
is to beat him
at his own game.

25:00.633 --> 25:04.566
♪ ♪

25:14.900 --> 25:20.666
(seagulls squawking,
breathing heavily)

25:20.666 --> 25:27.766
♪ ♪

25:41.066 --> 25:44.333
MRS. WHEATLEY:
You had us worried sick,
Miss Colbourne.

25:51.833 --> 25:53.800
Mr. Colbourne?

25:53.800 --> 25:56.200
He wanted one last word
with Colonel Lennox.

25:56.200 --> 25:58.000
But all is well?

25:58.000 --> 26:02.300
All is well.

26:02.300 --> 26:04.466
(seagulls squawking outside)

26:07.066 --> 26:08.800
(horse whinnying outside)

26:08.800 --> 26:11.900
GEORGIANA:
Lockhart is a disgrace.

26:11.900 --> 26:13.900
If only I'd seen
these sooner.

26:13.900 --> 26:16.000
Georgiana,

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
there's something else
you should know.

26:19.233 --> 26:22.233
Something Sidney mentioned
in his letter to Tom.

26:22.233 --> 26:24.700
What is it?

26:24.700 --> 26:28.400
In the process of building
his case against Mr. Lockhart,

26:28.400 --> 26:33.500
Sidney learned that contrary
to what you believe,

26:33.500 --> 26:37.033
your mother did not die
when you were a child.

26:37.033 --> 26:39.233
As recently
as five years ago,

26:39.233 --> 26:43.166
she was still hoping
you might be reunited.

26:43.166 --> 26:45.300
She left you this
to remember her by.

26:45.300 --> 26:48.200
♪ ♪

26:58.800 --> 26:59.900
Sidney tried to ascertain

26:59.900 --> 27:02.866
your mother's present
whereabouts,

27:02.866 --> 27:05.033
with no success.

27:05.033 --> 27:07.800
But there's every reason

27:07.800 --> 27:10.100
to believe that
she's still alive.

27:12.300 --> 27:16.433
(sobbing)

27:16.433 --> 27:19.600
(softly):
My dear...

27:19.600 --> 27:22.366
♪ ♪

27:22.366 --> 27:23.333
Colonel.

27:23.333 --> 27:25.233
Not now, Parker,
I'm not in the mood.

27:25.233 --> 27:28.266
Uh, I'm sorry, what I have
to say will not wait.

27:29.900 --> 27:31.966
In the guise of friendship,
you and your men

27:31.966 --> 27:33.800
have taken gross advantage

27:33.800 --> 27:35.233
of this town.

27:35.233 --> 27:37.500
You behaved abominably
towards Miss Heywood.

27:37.500 --> 27:39.766
You insulted me
and my family.

27:39.766 --> 27:42.333
And I will not stand for it.

27:44.033 --> 27:48.066
What are you going to do?

27:48.066 --> 27:52.966
You claim to be
a man of honor.

27:52.966 --> 27:54.233
I ask you now to prove it.

27:56.800 --> 27:58.500
(laughs)

27:58.500 --> 28:00.133
Are you...

28:00.133 --> 28:01.600
Are you
challenging me to a duel?

28:04.733 --> 28:07.033
Here is the money
I owe you.

28:07.033 --> 28:09.566
100 pounds.
(soldiers whispering)

28:09.566 --> 28:12.000
You can take it
right now.

28:12.000 --> 28:13.033
Or...

28:13.033 --> 28:14.566
Or...

28:14.566 --> 28:17.933
You can accept
my wager.

28:17.933 --> 28:18.900
What's the stake?

28:18.900 --> 28:22.900
If you win,
you keep our money,

28:22.900 --> 28:25.466
and I shall honor the
shopkeepers' debts myself.

28:25.466 --> 28:26.700
And if you win?

28:26.700 --> 28:28.366
Then you will pay every penny

28:28.366 --> 28:29.800
that you owe the town,

28:29.800 --> 28:31.333
you will write off my debt,

28:31.333 --> 28:34.300
and you will leave Sanditon,
never to return.

28:38.233 --> 28:40.200
Very well.

28:40.200 --> 28:41.166
One round of hazard.

28:41.166 --> 28:42.333
ARTHUR:
Ah...

28:43.400 --> 28:45.200
No.

28:45.200 --> 28:48.366
This time,
we choose the game.

28:48.366 --> 28:53.533
♪ ♪

29:04.466 --> 29:11.066
♪ ♪

29:19.866 --> 29:26.733
♪ ♪

29:26.733 --> 29:28.833
ARTHUR:
Colonel.

29:28.833 --> 29:31.600
Will you stand
or choose another card?

29:31.600 --> 29:33.933
♪ ♪

29:40.100 --> 29:41.700
(exhales)

29:42.766 --> 29:44.666
♪ ♪

29:44.666 --> 29:47.000
My late brother and I
could never agree on

29:47.000 --> 29:48.066
the nature of this game.

29:48.066 --> 29:52.933
I've always thought
it was a game of luck.

29:52.933 --> 29:56.866
But he claimed
it demands strategy.

29:56.866 --> 30:00.566
LENNOX:
If I put all my faith in luck,
I'd be long dead.

30:00.566 --> 30:03.200
As would most of my men.

30:03.200 --> 30:05.833
(knocks on table)

30:14.200 --> 30:15.533
♪ ♪

30:15.533 --> 30:17.200
ARTHUR:
Tom.

30:18.666 --> 30:25.333
♪ ♪

30:30.933 --> 30:31.900
Then again,

30:31.900 --> 30:34.066
I never won a game
against Sidney.

30:35.766 --> 30:38.033
So I have to concede
he may have been right.

30:38.033 --> 30:43.100
♪ ♪

30:50.400 --> 30:52.066
(exhales)

30:54.133 --> 30:57.666
♪ ♪

31:03.066 --> 31:04.733
20.

31:04.733 --> 31:06.766
(soldiers murmuring)
So, Colonel.

31:06.766 --> 31:08.366
Can you match me?

31:08.366 --> 31:10.666
Or do you surrender?

31:10.666 --> 31:16.833
♪ ♪

31:20.000 --> 31:22.200
(gasping, soldiers groan)

31:22.200 --> 31:23.766
ARTHUR:
19.

31:23.766 --> 31:25.100
Game to Mr. Parker.

31:25.100 --> 31:28.333
(laughing)

31:32.500 --> 31:33.900
Please.

31:33.900 --> 31:36.733
Here you go.

31:36.733 --> 31:39.566
Feed your families.

31:41.566 --> 31:44.200
You did the
Parker name proud.

31:44.200 --> 31:46.000
You did Sidney proud.

31:46.000 --> 31:48.033
No, Arthur, we did.

31:48.033 --> 31:50.833
♪ ♪

31:50.833 --> 31:53.700
(crowd applauding)

31:53.700 --> 31:55.333
(crowd exclaiming)

31:57.900 --> 31:59.366
CARTER:
Short honeymoon, Denham?

31:59.366 --> 32:00.933
I came to the conclusion
marriage isn't for me.

32:00.933 --> 32:03.100
Denham!

32:04.433 --> 32:09.066
Your aunt writes to inform me
of your recent conduct

32:09.066 --> 32:12.300
and that you have no means
of paying for your commission.

32:14.900 --> 32:18.633
You are a disgrace
to yourself and the company!

32:20.633 --> 32:24.866
You're not fit
to call yourself an officer.

32:24.866 --> 32:26.466
Out of my way!

32:26.466 --> 32:28.700
(horse whinnying in distance)

32:39.266 --> 32:41.900
ARTHUR:
Your sunny presence
will be much missed.

32:41.900 --> 32:42.900
(Alison laughing)

32:42.900 --> 32:43.900
TOM:
You are always welcome.

32:43.900 --> 32:45.600
MARY:
We will miss you, my dear.

32:45.600 --> 32:48.466
ALISON:
I will miss you all dreadfully.
(laughs)

32:50.166 --> 32:51.800
You must be sure to write
at least once a week.

32:51.800 --> 32:52.900
GEORGIANA:
I am sorry you did not

32:52.900 --> 32:54.833
get to say goodbye
to Captain Fraser.

32:54.833 --> 32:57.233
As a matter of fact,
he called on me earlier.

32:57.233 --> 32:58.900
What did he say?

32:58.900 --> 33:01.466
He said he'd grown to
consider me a dear friend.

33:01.466 --> 33:02.866
Friend?

33:02.866 --> 33:04.800
ALISON:
And he gave me a small gift
to remember him by,

33:04.800 --> 33:08.433
but made me swear I wouldn't
open it until I got home.

33:08.433 --> 33:13.000
♪ ♪

33:18.266 --> 33:22.300
♪ ♪

33:24.500 --> 33:27.133
It is a book of poetry.

33:27.133 --> 33:30.133
There is a flower
marking a page.

33:30.133 --> 33:31.566
♪ ♪

33:31.566 --> 33:34.400
This is the poem
William sent me.

33:34.400 --> 33:37.066
"Her face, it bloomed
like a sweet flower

33:37.066 --> 33:41.500
and stole my heart away."

33:41.500 --> 33:43.266
♪ ♪

33:43.266 --> 33:44.633
Except it wasn't William.

33:44.633 --> 33:48.566
It was, it was Captain Fraser.

33:51.500 --> 33:53.266
It was always him.

33:53.266 --> 33:55.300
This was not given
in friendship, Alison.

33:55.300 --> 33:58.200
♪ ♪

33:58.200 --> 34:00.200
(chuckles)

34:00.200 --> 34:03.466
♪ ♪

34:08.966 --> 34:11.466
What will I say to him?

34:11.466 --> 34:13.266
Tell him he has
won your heart,

34:13.266 --> 34:16.133
just as you have won his.

34:16.133 --> 34:19.333
Could it be that my cynical
sister's heart has softened?

34:19.333 --> 34:23.466
♪ ♪

34:31.666 --> 34:32.633
Excuse me, sir.

34:32.633 --> 34:34.466
I'm looking for
Captain Fraser.

34:34.466 --> 34:36.100
Gone, miss.

34:36.100 --> 34:37.633
All of them.

34:37.633 --> 34:39.200
Posted to India.

34:39.200 --> 34:44.366
♪ ♪

34:50.866 --> 34:53.033
India?

34:57.866 --> 35:01.966
♪ ♪

35:01.966 --> 35:07.133
(birds twittering)

35:09.133 --> 35:12.600
All my fears that he would
abandon me,

35:12.600 --> 35:14.266
that he stopped loving me,

35:14.266 --> 35:16.133
they were just

35:16.133 --> 35:18.300
ghosts in my mind,
nothing more.

35:18.300 --> 35:20.333
Placed there
by me and Edward.

35:20.333 --> 35:22.800
(George cooing)

35:22.800 --> 35:26.666
Edward exploited you.

35:26.666 --> 35:27.666
He's incapable of feeling.

35:27.666 --> 35:29.600
I am no different.

35:29.600 --> 35:32.900
I've seen the way
you look at George.

35:32.900 --> 35:35.000
(cooing)

35:35.000 --> 35:38.766
I have never known love like it,
Esther.

35:38.766 --> 35:41.300
It is so fierce
that it scares me.

35:41.300 --> 35:45.733
I hope one day you will
discover it for yourself.

35:45.733 --> 35:48.400
It's not meant to be.

35:48.400 --> 35:50.200
All the herbs and tinctures
in the world cannot help me.

35:50.200 --> 35:53.233
I shall just have to
make my peace with it.

35:53.233 --> 35:57.366
Lady Denham has been kind enough
to offer me a cottage

35:57.366 --> 36:00.000
on an estate in Cumbria,

36:00.000 --> 36:04.266
far from prying eyes
and the taint of scandal.

36:04.266 --> 36:05.766
Will you take her up on it?

36:05.766 --> 36:09.166
What kind of life
will it be for George?

36:09.166 --> 36:13.366
Growing up miles from anywhere,
with only me for company.

36:13.366 --> 36:15.800
As long as he is loved,

36:15.800 --> 36:18.533
what else matters?

36:18.533 --> 36:20.866
(coos)

36:22.733 --> 36:27.233
♪ ♪

36:27.233 --> 36:29.033
We missed him.

36:33.100 --> 36:34.266
Ah.

36:35.733 --> 36:37.766
Here she is now.

36:37.766 --> 36:38.933
(door closes)

36:38.933 --> 36:43.066
Is it not a
strange coincidence?

36:43.066 --> 36:46.266
Each of you
was seeking the other.

36:46.266 --> 36:48.366
♪ ♪

36:48.366 --> 36:50.066
MARY:
Thomas?
Yes, dear?

36:50.066 --> 36:51.966
♪ ♪

36:51.966 --> 36:53.733
Ah! Yes.
(chuckles)

36:53.733 --> 36:56.766
Yes, come, Arthur,
yes, we must, yes...
(clears throat)

36:59.533 --> 37:02.133
They told me your company
had left.

37:02.133 --> 37:03.133
They have.

37:03.133 --> 37:05.733
I resigned my commission.

37:05.733 --> 37:08.000
What will you do?

37:08.000 --> 37:10.466
I have no idea.

37:10.466 --> 37:12.100
I'm from a family of farmers
in Ireland.

37:12.100 --> 37:16.000
(laughing)

37:17.300 --> 37:19.533
Why should that be so funny?

37:19.533 --> 37:20.700
(laughing)

37:22.633 --> 37:26.766
I was always so determined I
would never be a farmer's wife.

37:26.766 --> 37:30.033
That seems
rather a presumption.

37:30.033 --> 37:33.500
I opened your book.

37:33.500 --> 37:34.566
A terrible breach of trust,

37:34.566 --> 37:36.633
given I explicitly
told you not to.

37:36.633 --> 37:38.266
I never should
have guessed

37:38.266 --> 37:42.200
that spartan Captain Fraser
could have such a poetic soul.

37:43.966 --> 37:46.600
Fool that I am,

37:46.600 --> 37:48.666
I have fought to hide
my feelings from you,

37:48.666 --> 37:52.333
believing them to be futile.

37:52.333 --> 37:55.366
Never daring to hope
that you could bring yourself

37:55.366 --> 37:59.500
to love a coarse,
battle-scarred soldier.

37:59.500 --> 38:01.900
But, my dearest Alison,

38:01.900 --> 38:05.433
I stand before you now
to ask you

38:05.433 --> 38:10.533
if you will honor me
with the greatest rank of all,

38:10.533 --> 38:12.400
that of your loving husband.

38:13.733 --> 38:14.700
Yes.

38:14.700 --> 38:16.100
Yes! Yes!

38:16.100 --> 38:17.900
100,000 times, yes!

38:17.900 --> 38:19.033
(laughs)

38:21.766 --> 38:28.200
♪ ♪

38:31.200 --> 38:32.666
(door opens)

38:32.666 --> 38:34.766
(Arthur laughing, clapping)

38:34.766 --> 38:36.600
(laughing, others clapping)

38:40.366 --> 38:45.266
(George crying loudly)

38:45.266 --> 38:47.033
Clara?

38:50.133 --> 38:52.766
(crying)

38:52.766 --> 38:54.666
Aw...

38:54.666 --> 38:58.100
(crying, Esther cooing)

38:58.100 --> 39:01.100
(crying stops)

39:01.100 --> 39:04.000
(George fussing)

39:05.666 --> 39:09.433
CLARA (voiceover):
Do not judge me too harshly.

39:09.433 --> 39:14.166
The fact is that some of us
are meant to be mothers,

39:14.166 --> 39:17.100
and some are not.

39:17.100 --> 39:20.833
He is yours now, Esther.

39:20.833 --> 39:25.000
You will give him the life
I never could.

39:25.000 --> 39:28.066
You will be the mother
he deserves.

39:28.066 --> 39:31.700
♪ ♪

39:31.700 --> 39:37.833
(birds twittering)

39:37.833 --> 39:43.000
♪ ♪

39:45.033 --> 39:46.200
CHARLOTTE:
Mrs. Wheatley.

39:46.200 --> 39:47.500
Good morning, Miss Heywood.

39:47.500 --> 39:50.200
You will find
your charges outside,

39:50.200 --> 39:52.133
having breakfast
with Mr. Colbourne.

39:52.133 --> 39:53.700
Together?

39:53.700 --> 39:57.066
Miracle of miracles,
wonder of wonders.

39:57.066 --> 39:58.933
♪ ♪

39:58.933 --> 40:02.666
COLBOURNE:
So, Luna has been telling me
that she's rather lonely.

40:02.666 --> 40:06.500
And she would like
a dog companion.

40:06.500 --> 40:08.500
That's what she told me.

40:08.500 --> 40:11.100
I was thinking perhaps
another lurcher?

40:12.066 --> 40:13.766
I should like a mastiff.

40:13.766 --> 40:15.566
(laughing)

40:15.566 --> 40:17.133
Good choice, Leo.

40:18.600 --> 40:20.200
Miss Heywood!

40:20.200 --> 40:22.833
We're going to get
a new dog.

40:22.833 --> 40:24.266
How exciting!

40:24.266 --> 40:26.233
Miss Heywood.

40:26.233 --> 40:28.066
I wondered if we might, um,

40:28.066 --> 40:30.933
speak in private.

40:32.633 --> 40:34.800
Of course.

40:36.200 --> 40:37.833
(seagulls squawking)

40:37.833 --> 40:39.933
GEORGIANA:
I don't suppose you'll change
your mind about marrying me.

40:39.933 --> 40:41.166
(Arthur laughs)

40:41.166 --> 40:44.666
Then I would never have to
consider the subject again.

40:44.666 --> 40:47.966
Thank you,
but I must decline again.

40:47.966 --> 40:49.366
(laughs)

40:49.366 --> 40:52.700
I am more convinced than ever
that marriage is not for me.

40:52.700 --> 40:56.100
Anyway, I firmly believe
the right man is waiting

40:56.100 --> 40:57.266
out there for you.

40:59.400 --> 41:00.800
In the middle of the sea?

41:00.800 --> 41:02.866
(laughs)

41:02.866 --> 41:04.200
(laughs)

41:04.200 --> 41:06.033
I meant figuratively.

41:08.633 --> 41:11.866
I blame myself,
you know.

41:11.866 --> 41:13.266
For Lockhart.

41:13.266 --> 41:17.500
You had your reservations
and I urged you to ignore them.

41:17.500 --> 41:21.133
I let his charm
get the better of me.

41:22.966 --> 41:24.833
He charmed us both, Arthur.

41:26.100 --> 41:27.900
You are not to blame.

41:29.266 --> 41:32.200
And he's gone now.

41:32.200 --> 41:35.333
Let us never
think of him again.

41:35.333 --> 41:37.066
♪ ♪

41:37.066 --> 41:40.400
Have you given any more thought
to what you will do

41:40.400 --> 41:41.833
when you come of age

41:41.833 --> 41:44.800
and inherit your fortune?

41:44.800 --> 41:47.700
For now, my only thought
is to find my mother.

41:47.700 --> 41:51.666
As for where I will go,
it is strange.

41:51.666 --> 41:52.933
Having longed
to escape Sanditon,

41:52.933 --> 41:54.666
I'm beginning to think
I might stay a while.

41:54.666 --> 41:56.566
(chuckles):
You must!

41:56.566 --> 41:57.600
After all,

41:57.600 --> 42:00.333
you're a part of our family.

42:00.333 --> 42:01.933
An honorary Parker!

42:01.933 --> 42:03.100
(chuckles)

42:05.566 --> 42:11.633
♪ ♪

42:15.600 --> 42:16.766
(door closes)
Miss Heywood...

42:20.466 --> 42:22.566
I owe you an apology.

42:22.566 --> 42:25.166
(laughing):
For what?

42:25.166 --> 42:27.500
My behavior has been
unforgivable.

42:27.500 --> 42:30.800
Twice I allowed my emotions
to get the better of me.

42:30.800 --> 42:33.833
Twice I have taken advantage
of my position over you.

42:36.100 --> 42:38.866
You make it sound as if I were
not a willing participant.

42:38.866 --> 42:41.200
You are the girls' governess
and I am master of the estate.

42:41.200 --> 42:42.566
I am your employer.

42:44.766 --> 42:45.766
It was deeply
inappropriate

42:45.766 --> 42:47.933
and I feel only shame
and regret.

42:50.566 --> 42:52.100
That is all I am to you?

42:54.100 --> 42:56.600
A member of your staff?

42:56.600 --> 43:00.200
In the circumstances,
I understand that your position

43:00.200 --> 43:01.333
here has become untenable

43:01.333 --> 43:06.500
and you will wish
to leave at once.

43:06.500 --> 43:09.000
I hope you'll accept six months
ex gratia to compensate you

43:09.000 --> 43:09.966
for the loss of earning.

43:09.966 --> 43:13.166
I don't care
about the money!

43:15.600 --> 43:16.766
What will you tell the girls?

43:18.133 --> 43:22.533
We shall say that your term
came to a natural conclusion

43:22.533 --> 43:24.833
by mutual agreement.

43:24.833 --> 43:26.633
No.

43:26.633 --> 43:29.633
This is your decision.

43:29.633 --> 43:30.966
And yours alone.

43:30.966 --> 43:36.133
♪ ♪

43:44.200 --> 43:46.100
Miss Heywood!

43:46.100 --> 43:47.666
Miss Heywood!

43:47.666 --> 43:50.500
&nbsp;
♪ ♪

43:57.833 --> 44:00.600
You will regret this.

44:00.600 --> 44:03.600
It's better this way.

44:03.600 --> 44:06.633
For her sake.

44:06.633 --> 44:08.366
Xander...

44:08.366 --> 44:10.200
Do not shut

44:10.200 --> 44:12.400
yourself away again.

44:12.400 --> 44:13.600
Please.

44:13.600 --> 44:19.000
♪ ♪

44:26.066 --> 44:28.666
(exhales)
My dear Lady Babington.

44:28.666 --> 44:30.033
We heard you were leaving.

44:30.033 --> 44:31.566
And we could not let
the moment pass

44:31.566 --> 44:33.666
without coming to bid you
bon voyage.

44:33.666 --> 44:36.300
Well, you could have.

44:36.300 --> 44:37.433
Thank you both.

44:37.433 --> 44:39.600
(George stirring)

44:41.600 --> 44:43.933
HANKINS:
But who is this?

44:43.933 --> 44:46.300
This is George.

44:48.233 --> 44:50.266
My son.

44:50.266 --> 44:55.766
♪ ♪

44:55.766 --> 44:57.900
(laughs)

44:59.866 --> 45:03.100
♪ ♪

45:03.100 --> 45:04.133
AUGUSTA:
What did you say to her?!

45:04.133 --> 45:05.533
That is not your concern.

45:05.533 --> 45:06.533
I saw her leaving!

45:06.533 --> 45:09.466
There are things
you do not understand!

45:09.466 --> 45:14.233
I understand that she
brought light into a house

45:14.233 --> 45:16.900
which before her
knew only darkness.

45:16.900 --> 45:19.200
I understand that she
brought us together.

45:19.200 --> 45:20.966
That she cared about me
and Leonora

45:20.966 --> 45:23.533
as if we were
her own sisters!

45:23.533 --> 45:27.233
I understand that she almost
restored you to a...

45:27.233 --> 45:30.333
To a human being.

45:31.466 --> 45:33.533
Are we to revert
to how things were?

45:33.533 --> 45:35.266
Augusta!

45:35.266 --> 45:37.933
Oh, what is it you are
frightened of, Uncle?

45:37.933 --> 45:40.100
That we might finally be happy?

45:40.100 --> 45:42.300
Go to her! Please!

45:42.300 --> 45:43.766
Ask her to come back!

45:43.766 --> 45:45.900
Tell her that you
made a mistake!

45:45.900 --> 45:47.433
For our sake,

45:47.433 --> 45:49.133
if not for your own.

45:49.133 --> 45:54.300
♪ ♪

46:05.500 --> 46:06.633
(footsteps approaching)

46:06.633 --> 46:12.166
♪ ♪

46:16.900 --> 46:19.300
Having had time to reflect,

46:19.300 --> 46:21.400
I've decided to
accept your offer.

46:21.400 --> 46:22.633
(chuckling)

46:22.633 --> 46:24.433
I thought you might.

46:24.433 --> 46:26.766
It seems marginally less
horrifying than debtor's prison.

46:26.766 --> 46:29.733
Oh, I wouldn't be so sure.

46:29.733 --> 46:32.600
And with Esther and Clara
safely dispatched,

46:32.600 --> 46:36.200
you shall have my
undivided attention.

46:36.200 --> 46:37.866
Where's my son?

46:37.866 --> 46:41.900
He's on his way
to a better life,

46:41.900 --> 46:46.266
far removed from his
wretched father.

46:51.633 --> 46:54.033
At least now that you're
no longer working,

46:54.033 --> 46:55.733
we can enjoy
the rest of the summer.

46:55.733 --> 46:58.433
Father expects me home.

46:58.433 --> 47:01.833
I've tried his patience
long enough.

47:01.833 --> 47:02.800
You have our friendship.

47:02.800 --> 47:05.333
Is that not reason enough
to stay?

47:05.333 --> 47:06.833
You can help me
find my mother.

47:06.833 --> 47:09.100
I hope I shall always have that,
Georgiana,

47:09.100 --> 47:10.966
whether or not we are
in the same place.

47:10.966 --> 47:14.533
And of course I'll do whatever
I can to help you find her.

47:14.533 --> 47:16.900
You'll be invited
to Alison's wedding,

47:16.900 --> 47:19.666
so it shan't be long before
we see each other again.

47:19.666 --> 47:21.600
I do wish you would stay.
(door opens)

47:21.600 --> 47:23.633
Charlotte.

47:23.633 --> 47:25.666
A Mr. Colbourne is here
to see you.

47:29.500 --> 47:30.933
I've been thinking on

47:30.933 --> 47:34.766
our conversation,
Miss Heywood.

47:34.766 --> 47:36.933
As have I.

47:36.933 --> 47:39.100
I came to tell you
that I regret

47:39.100 --> 47:42.400
the circumstances under which
we parted company.

47:42.400 --> 47:45.433
You made yourself very clear.

47:45.433 --> 47:47.533
Augusta's rightly furious
with me.

47:47.533 --> 47:49.400
She urged me to come and
speak with you at once.

47:49.400 --> 47:51.566
Then you are here
at Augusta's request.

47:51.566 --> 47:52.700
Not of your own volition?

47:52.700 --> 47:55.500
No.

47:55.500 --> 47:59.600
The house
feels your absence already.

48:02.433 --> 48:03.800
And I'm here to ask if you...

48:03.800 --> 48:06.100
I'm resolved to leave Sanditon,
Mr. Colbourne.

48:06.100 --> 48:09.200
♪ ♪

48:09.200 --> 48:12.466
You were right in what you said.

48:12.466 --> 48:15.666
We let our emotions
get the better of us.

48:16.900 --> 48:20.366
I mistook what I was feeling
for a certain kind of affection.

48:20.366 --> 48:22.266
But I realize now I,

48:22.266 --> 48:24.000
I could never feel
such tenderness for a man

48:24.000 --> 48:26.333
who showed me
so little respect.

48:26.333 --> 48:28.933
♪ ♪

48:28.933 --> 48:31.766
I will miss the girls
a great deal.

48:31.766 --> 48:34.466
But I cannot be your governess,

48:34.466 --> 48:37.433
if that is what you came to ask.

48:37.433 --> 48:44.166
♪ ♪

48:46.433 --> 48:48.833
Thank you

48:48.833 --> 48:52.100
for making
your feelings so clear.

48:52.100 --> 48:58.466
♪ ♪

49:06.966 --> 49:09.166
(sobs)

49:09.166 --> 49:11.666
♪ ♪

49:11.666 --> 49:12.833
(exhales)

49:16.866 --> 49:19.366
Enough!

49:21.833 --> 49:25.233
(sniffles)

49:28.366 --> 49:33.400
Wilt thou have this man
to thy wedded husband,

49:33.400 --> 49:37.366
live together
after God's ordinance

49:37.366 --> 49:39.733
in the holy estate
of matrimony?

49:41.733 --> 49:44.666
Wilt thou obey him

49:44.666 --> 49:46.200
and serve him,

49:46.200 --> 49:49.033
love, honor, and keep him,

49:49.033 --> 49:50.566
and, forsaking

49:50.566 --> 49:54.666
all other,
keep thee only unto him,

49:54.666 --> 49:56.366
so long as ye both

49:56.366 --> 49:58.033
shall live?

49:58.033 --> 50:00.066
I will.

50:00.066 --> 50:01.800
(crowd murmuring)

50:01.800 --> 50:06.100
♪ ♪

50:14.366 --> 50:17.133
(church bells tolling)

50:17.133 --> 50:19.800
(crowd cheering)

50:19.800 --> 50:26.200
♪ ♪

50:34.800 --> 50:36.366
How long will we be gone,
Father?

50:37.733 --> 50:40.933
I cannot say.

50:42.133 --> 50:45.066
We've been confined here
too long.

50:45.066 --> 50:47.233
We need a change.

50:47.233 --> 50:48.233
All of us.

50:48.233 --> 50:54.133
♪ ♪

51:08.900 --> 51:14.066
(band playing dance tune)

51:24.200 --> 51:27.733
(tune continues)

51:31.633 --> 51:34.233
You must come and stay with us
again soon, my dear.

51:34.233 --> 51:36.233
All of our sea view apartments
have been taken--

51:36.233 --> 51:37.900
even one by Georgiana.

51:37.900 --> 51:40.133
Sanditon goes from
strength to strength.

51:40.133 --> 51:42.233
I shall be holding a party
for my 21st birthday.

51:42.233 --> 51:43.833
Promise you will return
for that.

51:43.833 --> 51:45.066
Forgive the interruption,

51:45.066 --> 51:47.466
but I believe I am promised
the next dance.

51:47.466 --> 51:50.233
May I introduce
Mr. Ralph Starling.

51:50.233 --> 51:52.966
Charlotte talks of you often
and with great fondness.

51:52.966 --> 51:55.000
I assume she's told you

51:55.000 --> 51:56.233
our happy news?

51:56.233 --> 51:58.566
What news is that?

51:58.566 --> 52:00.866
Ralph and I are to be married.

52:00.866 --> 52:05.966
&nbsp;
(tune continues)

52:15.933 --> 52:20.466
♪ ♪

